{
  "stem": "25598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So in this hut there were-- there were five people living before, which was a very old lady who we called her babushka.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I never knew what-- nobody ever knew what her name was, because that's how she was called.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then there was her daughter-in-law, who was Bella, who was an absolutely gorgeous, absolutely gorgeous young woman-- black hair, black eyes, carried herself like a queen.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she had one son, Tosia, who looked very much like her.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was 10 years old-- my age-- gorgeous, but stupid.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- [LAUGHS] --that was from her first marriage.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then she had another son, a five-year-old, with this second husband, who was the real grandchild of babushka.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was a redhead, and freckled, and ugly, and smart like 10 devils, and behaved like 10 devils.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, he knew everything-- what's going on in-- in the huts around us, and where to steal, and what to get, and what to-- and-- and-- he was our lifeline, like with the outside world.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We did not stay in the same hut with my Auntie Mila, and my Uncle Armin, and my grandmother, and-- and neither with my paternal grandparents.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We stayed with some-- some other people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] And then we started running out of money.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that's when the barter system took off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Barter means you exchange a pair of shoes, for example, for a carton of potatoes, or a shirt, or a coat for a-- a little bag of flour, or for some beets, or-- or what have you.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had it not so bad, because [NON-ENGLISH] who was Beile's husband, who was taken into the Soviet army, he used to work in some kind of a [NON-ENGLISH] which is a collective Soviet farm.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
